Inter-VLAN Routing & Static Routing Lab
Overview

This project demonstrates the implementation of Inter-VLAN Routing and Static Routing using Cisco Packet Tracer.

The network is divided into multiple VLANs representing different departments, and communication is enabled across VLANs and routers.

 Topology Description
3 Routers connected via:
192.168.1.0/24
172.168.1.0/16
3 Switches (Layer 2)
9 End Devices (PCs)
VLANs:
VLAN 10 → Sales → 10.0.0.0/8
VLAN 20 → HR → 20.0.0.0/8
VLAN 30 → IT → 30.0.0.0/8

Technologies Used
VLAN Configuration
Trunking (802.1Q)
Inter-VLAN Routing (Router-on-a-Stick)
Static Routing
IP Addressing

Configuration Summary
Switch
VLANs created
Access ports assigned
Trunk port configured toward router

-Router
Subinterfaces created using dot1Q
Gateway IP assigned for each VLAN

-Routing
Static routes configured between routers for full connectivity
-IP Addressing Table
Device	IP Address	Network
VLAN 10 Gateway	10.0.0.1	10.0.0.0/8
VLAN 20 Gateway	20.0.0.1	20.0.0.0/8
VLAN 30 Gateway	30.0.0.1	30.0.0.0/8

